   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Storytelling as a catalyst to promote literacy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Purpose: Using the love of stories as a catalyst to promote a culture of reading for pleasure, as the foundation for literacy and learning. Concept: Build on the highly innovative 1 Telling Stories of KwaZulu-Natal ` project and its extension into 24 rural schools into KZN South Africa, through which 66000 school kids have been involved in storytelling and literacy activities at libraries and schools. Rationale: In rural KZN, there is no culture, and very few people read for pleasure.</narrative>
  </description>
